20/09/2010
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Eduard Kukan, chairman of the European Parliament (EP) delegation for relations with Southeast European countries, warned on Sunday (September 19th) that organised crime and corruption issues could endanger Montenegro's path to the EU. In an interview with MINA news agency, Kukan also voiced hope that the government and parliament will do their best to avoid such a scenario. Kukan called on the cabinet to step up efforts in fighting these phenomena. He also stressed the importance of engaging the public in the decision-making process concerning EU integration. (MINA, RTCG, Portal Analitika - 19/09/10)
